description:
&lt;p&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust invite candidates to apply for a Trust Doctor (ST3-7 equivalent) post in Intensive Care Medicine to join the Department based at Hammersmith Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is to commence from 1st March 2021 for a fixed term period until the 1st September 2021 renewable for 6 months until the 1st March 2022.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will become part of a friendly team of Trainee Doctors from Medicine, Anaesthesia, Surgery and Accident and Emergency Medicine and could be from a background in any of these specialities. Previous experience in Intensive Care Medicine and/or Anaesthesia is essential&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be registered with General Medical Council and have a licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;====================================================================&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non UK / EEA applicants should ensure that they are aware of recent changes to the immigration rules for Postgraduate Doctors and Dentists. For further information on how this may affect your application please contact the Home Office&#39;s Immigration and Nationality Enquiry Bureau on telephone: 0870 606 7766 or by e-mail: &lt;strong&gt;indpublicenquiries@ind.homeoffice.gsi.gov.uk &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Late applications will not be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promoting Equal Opportunities and a Smoke Free Environment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Umeer Waheed by e-mail Umeer.waheed@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
